Katsina State Police Command said it has rescued six kidnapped teenage girls in Batsari Local Government Area (LGA) of the state. A statement issued in Katsina on Thursday by the command’s spokesman, SP Gambo Isah, stated that the victims were kidnapped while working in a farm at Mata-Mulki Village in Batsari. Isah said that the police received a distress call at about 12:30 p.m. that “unrepentant bandits with AK47 rifles kidnapped some girls working in a farm at Mata-Mulki Village.” 2023 : Group backs Olabode George for president Workers’ support, prayers instrumental to our… Gov Bello extols virtues of late Aduku, Nigeria’s oldest war… Demolition of Saraki’s property cowardly ― PDP ALSO READ: Nigeria deserves better road network ― Rep member, Okechukwu He said that the Operation Puff Adder team, led by Divisional Police Officer in charge of Batsari, swiftly moved to the area. “The team gave the hoodlums a hot chase into the forest and engaged them in a gun duel. “The bandits abandoned the victims and ran into the forest, the police successfully rescued the six girls,” Isah said. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
